The paper deals with the computation and maintenance of a geometric structure (the geodesic Voronoi diagram) in the presence of motion, which is a classic problem in computational geometry and falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also develops a kinetic data structure (KDS) to maintain the Voronoi diagram, which is a subfield of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the analysis of the number of events where the Voronoi diagram changes, which is related to the study of combinatorial structures (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the KDS, which is related to the field of algorithms and complexity (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the maintenance of a geometric structure inside a polygon, which is related to the field of computational geometry and graph theory (cs.GR).
